news.title: S2W Media Deepens Global Footprint with Strategic Move to Pune’s AP4 Tech Park
news.para: The global B2B demand-generation leader reinforces its India commitment with a 50,000 sq. ft. space at Amar Builders & Pristine Properties' flagship development.

news.title: Property tax rebate window closes today, Ludhiana mayor plea to avoid 20% hit
news.para: Ludhiana offers a 10% property tax rebate for payments made by September 30 for FY 2025-26. City leaders stressed timely payments are crucial for development. Penalties for late payments begin October 1, escalating to 20% plus 18% annual interest after March 31.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body allows property tax rebate for one more month
news.para: Ghaziabad Municipal Corporation has extended its property tax rebate deadline to October 31, offering a 20% discount to maximise revenue. Subsequent rebates will be 10% in November 2025 and 5% for December and January 2026, before fines apply. With over 5.50 lakh taxpayers, GMC aims to collect 80% of the state's Rs 600 crore target for FY 2025-26.

news.title: PM Svamitva Yojana brings legal ownership & financial empowerment to rural Andhra Pradesh
news.para: Rural Andhra Pradesh families lacked land ownership documents for generations. The PM Svamitva Yojana now addresses this issue. Advanced technology like drones maps village properties precisely. This scheme provides legal ownership certificates to villagers. It resolves disputes and enables financial independence. The initiative also identifies government lands and boosts local panchayat revenue.

news.title: Under proposed law, tenants could be fined ₹50,000 for illegally subletting property
news.para: Karnataka has amended its Rent Control Act, decriminalising rental disputes by removing imprisonment clauses. This move, aligning with the Jan Vishwas Act, introduces hefty fines ranging from 900% to 2,500% for violations like unauthorised subletting or illegal eviction. Rent controllers will now adjudicate disputes, aiming to reduce judicial burden.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's 50% discount on temporary leases causes it ₹23 crore loss
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation incurred a Rs 23 crore loss by offering a 50% discount on temporary plot leases, effectively negating the new jantri rates. Despite the state government doubling land valuation, the AMC's standing committee rejected a proposal to increase the discounted rent, leading to an annual loss of Rs 10-12 crore.

news.title: Housing board to hike circle rates for two Ghaziabad townships
news.para: UP Housing Board hiked circle rates in Vasundhara and Siddharth Vihar townships, effective retrospectively from April 1, 2025-26. Increases of Rs 7,000-9,000 per sqm impact residential and commercial properties, raising affordability concerns for thousands. This move aligns with new building bylaws and improved connectivity, though low-income housing rates remain unchanged.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA website down in prime season of property deals
news.para: Rajasthan's RERA website has been dysfunctional for a month, leaving homebuyers unable to verify project registrations during the festive season. Developers are also struggling to upload new projects and submit mandatory audit reports by the September 30 deadline. This disruption is due to the transition to RERA 2.0, with officials expecting full functionality within 7-8 days.

news.title: Supreme Court summons Bhubaneswar development body over certificate issuance
news.para: The Supreme Court has summoned the Bhubaneswar Development Authority over a contentious occupancy certificate issued for Odisha's first PPP real estate project. This project is embroiled in legal battles due to alleged fraudulent practices and regulatory oversights, including an OC granted for incomplete construction.

news.title: Dues not cleared, Noida authority cancels company’s Sports City land after nine-year wait
news.para: Noida Authority has cancelled the allotment of 1.1 lakh sqm of land to Lotus Greens Constructions for its Sports City project in Sector 150. This action follows nine years of unpaid land dues despite repeated reminders, marking the first such cancellation against a Sports City developer.

news.title: Nagpur: About 862-acres proposed to be excised from Kamptee defence area
news.para: A draft plan proposes freeing nearly 862 acres from Kamptee Cantonment's military control for real estate development under Yerkheda Nagar Panchayat. The proposal awaits state government approval before the Ministry of Defence makes a final decision. This excision aims to dismantle the cantonment board, though the Mall area remains under military control for now.

news.title: Sahara firm seeks SC nod for sale of group's assets to Adani properties
news.para: Sahara India Commercial Corporation Ltd (SICCL) has sought Supreme Court approval to sell major properties, including Amby Valley, to Adani Properties Private Limited. This crucial step aims to expedite asset liquidation and repay investors, particularly following the death of Sahara chief Subrata Roy.

news.title: Ex-director of Lodha Developers sent to 14-day judicial custody in fraud case
news.para: Former Lodha Developers director Rajendra Lodha was sent to 14-day judicial custody in an alleged Rs 85 crore fraud case, with police denied further remand. Arrested for colluding to sell company assets at reduced rates, Lodha faces charges of criminal breach of trust.

news.title: WeWork India sets price band at ₹615-648 per share for ₹3,000 crore IPO
news.para: WeWork India announced its IPO price band at Rs 615-648 per share for a Rs 3,000 crore Offer-for-Sale, valuing the company at Rs 8,685 crore. Opening October 3, the issue is entirely an OFS by the promoter and WeWork Global, aiming for listing benefits and liquidity for existing shareholders, with proceeds going to selling entities.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA orders punitive action against multiple builders
news.para: UP-RERA has ordered strict action against multiple promoters, including Mahagun and Mahalaxmi Groups, for various RERA Act violations following homebuyer complaints. Breaches ranged from misrepresenting documents and failing to issue proper allotment letters to violating orders and presenting misleading facts. The authority aims to reinforce buyer trust and transparency.

news.title: KSH INFRA & WSB Real Estate to develop 50-acre logistics park in Bengaluru
news.para: KSH INFRA and WSB Real Estate Partners, along with co-investors, are developing a 50-acre industrial and logistics park in Hosur, Bengaluru. This ₹450 crore project, launched last year, will offer 1.25 million sq ft of space and create over 1,800 jobs. WSB and co-investors hold a 74% stake in the asset-level joint venture.

news.title: Hiranandani group launches 225-acres township in Alibaug
news.para: Hiranandani Communities launched its Hiranandani Sands township in Alibaug, Maharashtra, spanning over 225 acres with a projected revenue of ₹17,000 crore. The first phase, comprising 330 units across three residential towers, recorded ₹450 crore in sales at launch.

news.title: Owners must pay area circle rate fixed by Goa government to regularise structures
news.para: Goa's government will regularize structures on state or comunidade land under the 'Majhe ghar' scheme, charging owners based on circle rates. A 2014 cut-off applies. The cabinet is finalizing taluka-specific rates, aiming for a swift decision before Union Home Minister Amit Shah launches the scheme.

news.title: Tumakuru, Shivamogga city corporations set to expand
news.para: The Karnataka government is significantly expanding Tumakuru and Shivamogga city corporations by incorporating surrounding villages. Tumakuru City Corporation will grow from 48sqkm to 174 sqkm, adding 54 villages, as these areas have lost their rural character. Shivamogga Municipal Corporation is also preparing a detailed proposal to include 19 villages that have urbanized.

news.title: Over 260 properties in Nagpur default on ₹442 crore tax
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation faces a severe financial crisis as 261 prime properties owe a staggering Rs 442.34 crore in property tax, with individual defaults exceeding Rs 25 lakh. This massive arrear, if recovered, could fund critical projects like the stalled Nag River Pollution Abatement Project. Activists criticize NMC's lax enforcement and political shielding of influential defaulters.
